Question:
A school is trying to take an annual photo of all the students. The students are asked to stand in a single file line in non-decreasing order by height. Let this ordering be represented by the integer array expected where expected[i] is the expected height of the ith student in line.

You are given an integer array heights representing the current order that the students are standing in. Each heights[i] is the height of the ith student in line (0-indexed).

Return the number of indices where heights[i] != expected[i].

 

Example 1:

Input: heights = [1,1,4,2,1,3]
Output: 3
Explanation: 
heights:  [1,1,4,2,1,3]
expected: [1,1,1,2,3,4]
Indices 2, 4, and 5 do not match.
Example 2:

Input: heights = [5,1,2,3,4]
Output: 5
Explanation:
heights:  [5,1,2,3,4]
expected: [1,2,3,4,5]
All indices do not match.

Burette fource approuch : deplicate the array ,sort it and compare to the original array

Solution:

class Solution {
    public int heightChecker(int[] heights) {
        int count = 0;
        int[] temp = new int[heights.length];
        for(int i=0;i<temp.length;i++){
            temp[i]=heights[i];
        }
        Arrays.sort(heights);
        for(int i=0;i<temp.length;i++){
            if(temp[i]!=heights[i]){
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count ;

        
    }
}

Time complexity : O(2NlogN)
Space complexity : O(N)

Optimal solution : Hashing method
Thinking : render all the  frequency of the element in a single array and use the index order to check the arrangement


class Solution {
    public int heightChecker(int[] heights) {
      int[] freq = new int[101];
      int len = heights.length;
      for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
        freq[heights[i]] = freq[heights[i]]+1;
      } 
      int index = 0;
      int total = 0;
      for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
        while(freq[index]==0){
            index++;
        }
        if(heights[i]!=index)total++;
        freq[index]--;
      }
      return total;
    }
}


Time complexity : O(n+100)
Space complexity : O(1)
